reviews.text: Good food with reasonable price for restaurant in Hong Kong
The staff can’t even point the correct booked table and food is below average. Will NOT recommend!
Though not near any major transport stations, with nice environment and valuable-of-price foods, you may be attracted to here and have a decent meal.

This restaurant is one of the best HK traditional food I ever had except the 流沙包， it's too greasy and below my expectation. 
Wash the chopsticks, bowl and plate by using the tea first, this is the eating in HK 101.
Nice food and service.

result.name: The South China Hotel

reviews.text: Can't complain. Price is good room clean and staff helpful. Close to transport although airport express bus does not stop here its only a 100 meter walk from the Ibis North point which has a stop

This hotel was decent - close to the MTR station and ferry, and has basically a door front drop off from the A11 bus from the airport which is nice.
The rooms were small and a bit dated. The beds were very hard to the point you could feel each spring of the mattress which isn't ideal - but if you like a hard bed you'll be just fine 
Overall perfectly decent stay for the cost.
Rooms are clean and more spacious than most Hong Kong hotels. But the room size is still a little small. Value for money.

Room 1409 is terrible!!! The bathroom has no door. The shower head is strong but targeting the sides and not the person below who is taking a shower. When we asked to change room they would lie that all rooms are fully booked. Fortunately we question them about a room whom we knew are checking out at that time. Quite a squabble then. Would you believe that they even requested that we just move in would be ok without any housekeeping till the next day! We knew hotel policies and operations that housekeeping can be done before 2pm! Which is also the time that you can start to check into a room also. It wouldn't take that long to do the cleaning when the former occupant checked out since that morning!

I couldn’t find any good things here except it’s close to MTR. 
Price is expensive, room is old & dirty with stiff bed.. 

Will never ever stay in this place.

result.adr_address: 香港北角渣華道67-75號
result.name: 粵華酒店

reviews.text:
出張で利用しました。築年数はそれなりのホテルだと思います。
MTRの北角から歩いて5分弱のホテルです。

隣には北角街市があり、ローカル中華ぎ食べれます。(個人的にオススメはその市場の中の東寶です。日本語メニューもあります。)

上層階に泊まると風呂場の水圧が弱く、シャワーが物足りないかもしれません。

宿泊客のほとんどは中国からの旅行客だと思います。

料金は、曜日にもよりますが1泊1万円に収まります。一部屋あたりの料金なので二人度泊まれば割安です。

朝食ブュッフェは少し残念なレパートリーしかありませんのであまり期待されない方が良いです。

坦白說以衛生程度來講高標的人不適合（本人親眼看到大毛巾有黑點跟頭髮）其它都普通，離北角港鐵算近，地面走路7分鐘左右就到。可坐機場巴士A11,A12都頗方便，到站走路到飯店也是大概10分鐘！
不過巴士大概開60分到90分不等，時間要抓一下。不是很熱鬧的地區但也別有一番老城區風味。

還可以，房間小
香港就是這樣 (ㆀ˘･з･˘)
樓下剛好在整修，所以...加油
可以更好的 (๑•̀ㅂ•́)و✧
有不少七天旅遊嘅大陸北姑居住，很雜和亂感覺。
Can't complain. Price is good room clean and staff helpful. Close to transport although airport express bus does not stop here its only a 100 meter walk from the Ibis North point which has a stop
